Comment:
To Whom it May Concern;

It is a public health concern that some airlines do not prohibit e-cigarettes on the aircrafts.  E-cigarettes are not regulated by the FDA and the dangers of e-cigarettes are truly not known.  It is known that e-cigarettes contain nicotine and carcinogens.  It is concerning that e-cigarette companies can "mix" their own e-liquid.  Who knows what is being emitted from the e-cigarettes when it is not regulated by the FDA?

Please prohibit all forms and types of e-cigarettes on airlines just as all other tobacco products have been prohibited.  Please protect the public and flight attendants from the hazards of all tobacco products including e-cigarettes.
